body:
I just found a bug in my RTL because this line had a 12 instead of a 13:

`
freq       = { 7'd0, fnum } + { {12{pm_offset[3]}}, pm_offset };
`

Surprisingly, Verilator linter is fine with a 12 and a 13. It will only issue warnings for numbers below 12 and above 13. The correct bit count occurs for 13. Is this behavior correct?

Here is the full, if short, module:

```
module jtopl_pg_inc (
    input        [ 2:0] block,
    input        [ 9:0] fnum,
    input signed [ 3:0] pm_offset,
    output reg   [16:0] phinc_pure
);

reg [16:0] freq;
/* verilator lint_on WIDTH */

always @(*) begin 
    freq       = { 7'd0, fnum } + { {12{pm_offset[3]}}, pm_offset };
    // Add PM here
    freq       = freq << block;
    phinc_pure = freq >> 1;
end

endmodule // jtopl_pg_inc
```
